    "body": "<!-- bos:work-item {\"acceptanceCriteria\":[\"gh cannot execute from an AgentRun even when called by absolute path or shell wrapper\",\"Direct api.github.com requests are blocked and audited\",\"Allowed git fetch and exact non-force push continue to work\",\"The block response names the appropriate bos-mcp operation\",\"Complete Symphony security and executor tests pass\"],\"autonomy\":\"full\",\"context\":\"During the bos-mcp#8 delivery coordinator turn, Codex executed a read-only gh pr list command even though WORKFLOW.md prohibits gh and requires all GitHub context and durable operations through bos-mcp. The command was audited and the actual PR creation still used bos-mcp, but prompt-only enforcement is insufficient.\",\"dependencies\":[6],\"expectedOutcome\":\"AgentRun shell execution rejects gh and direct GitHub REST/GraphQL access before process launch, records a policy AuditEvent, and directs Codex to the corresponding bos-mcp domain tool.\",\"kind\":\"issue\",\"operationId\":\"op_symphony_block_direct_github_tools_20260721\",\"outOfScope\":[\"Block ordinary Git transport\",\"Rely only on prompt wording\",\"Expose GitHub tokens to the runner\"],\"parentIssueNumber\":null,\"risk\":\"critical\",\"scope\":[\"Block gh executable invocation inside AgentRuns\",\"Block curl, wget and SDK calls targeting api.github.com or graphql endpoints where detectable\",\"Allow Git local clone, fetch and guarded push according to policy\",\"Record requested command, redacted policy reason and suggested bos-mcp replacement\",\"Add adversarial quoting, absolute-path and shell-wrapper tests\",\"Keep human host administration outside AgentRuns separately governed\"],\"status\":\"ready\",\"title\":\"Enforce the BOS integration boundary in the instrumented command executor\"} -->\n\n## Context\n\nDuring the bos-mcp#8 delivery coordinator turn, Codex executed a read-only gh pr list command even though WORKFLOW.md prohibits gh and requires all GitHub context and durable operations through bos-mcp. The command was audited and the actual PR creation still used bos-mcp, but prompt-only enforcement is insufficient.\n\n## Expected outcome\n\nAgentRun shell execution rejects gh and direct GitHub REST/GraphQL access before process launch, records a policy AuditEvent, and directs Codex to the corresponding bos-mcp domain tool.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Block gh executable invocation inside AgentRuns\n- Block curl, wget and SDK calls targeting api.github.com or graphql endpoints where detectable\n- Allow Git local clone, fetch and guarded push according to policy\n- Record requested command, redacted policy reason and suggested bos-mcp replacement\n- Add adversarial quoting, absolute-path and shell-wrapper tests\n- Keep human host administration outside AgentRuns separately governed\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Block ordinary Git transport\n- Rely only on prompt wording\n- Expose GitHub tokens to the runner\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- gh cannot execute from an AgentRun even when called by absolute path or shell wrapper\n- Direct api.github.com requests are blocked and audited\n- Allowed git fetch and exact non-force push continue to work\n- The block response names the appropriate bos-mcp operation\n- Complete Symphony security and executor tests pass\n",
